---
description: API type layout conventions for this repo. Apply when editing api/v*/**/*_types.go, and when deciding type ordering or where helpers belong. Apply when editing relevant files, and when reasoning/planning/answering questions where this rule could influence code decisions (even if matching files are not currently open).
globs: api/v*/**/*_types.go
alwaysApply: false
---

- Type order in `<object>_types.go` (MUST):
  - `type <Obj> struct`
  - `type <Obj>List struct`
  - `type <Obj>Spec struct`
  - Spec-local types/helpers
  - `type <Obj>Status struct`
  - Status-local types/helpers

- List placement (MUST):
  - `<Obj>List` appears immediately after `<Obj>`.

- Helpers (MUST):
  - Keep helpers pure and local to the object type.
  - Non-trivial/domain logic belongs outside `*_types.go`.

- Shared API types (MUST):
  - If a type is used by more than one API object, it MUST live in `common_types.go`.
  - Do NOT duplicate shared types across `*_types.go` files.

- Required fields (MUST):
  - Fields that are required for the API MUST NOT use `omitempty`.
  - Add kubebuilder validation markers (e.g., `MinLength`, `Enum`) for required scalars.

- Enum constants (MUST):
  - API-level enums/constants live in the `api` package.
  - Controller/domain enums live in the `domain` package.
